The paper deals with information theory, specifically the rate-distortion function for Gaussian stationary sources. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and filtering, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), or cs.SP (Signal Processing). Finally, the paper discusses the design of coding schemes, which could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
